# BASIC
1. to view all facial components, including the image and description --> done
2. to select face/mouth/eyes/hairdo & preview the emojitar image --> done
3. to save a newly created emojitar to the server (must: unique id, descrip, creator, created-date/time) --> done 
4. to view all existing emojitars (must: image, creator, description) --> done
5. to comment & rate a specific emojitar (must: commenter, commented-date/time)-->220030280-server
6. to view a sepcific emojitar (must: image, creator, description, all:commenter's name/rate/comments)--> done


# INTERMEDIATE
1. function for all users
    1.1 to view all emojitars with specific criteria (e.g. creator or create on/after date)
    1.2 to view existing emojitars / associated comments / build / preview new emojitars
    1.3 to register and login
2. function only for logged users
   2.1 to save emojitar
   2.2 to comment/rate emojitars other user created
   2.2 to delete their own emijotars (must: relevent files and comments...)

# ADVANCE
1. function for all users
    1.1 to customise a facial component(e.g. tint the colour of face/eye/hair)
2. function for logged users
    2.1 to upload a new facial component
         @ must: type, image, id, description, creator, save-date/time
         @ preview before upload
         @ verify: file type, maximum file size, image dimensions(240x240 pixel, PNG, transparency)

# API
Node.js Tutorial: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TcvOgwQPsSo

The API should provide services including, but not limited to:
• Getting all facial components. (done, 10 March, 220005874)
• Creating a new emojitar.
• Getting all existing emojitars.
• Getting a specific emojitar along with its comments & ratrings.
• Commenting on & rating an existing emojitar.